title: Live coverage: SpaceX to launch its Falcon 9 rocket on midday Starlink mission from Cape Canaveral
summary: The Starlink 6-96 mission will add another 29 broadband internet satellites to the low Earth orbit constellation. Liftoff is scheduled for 1:29 p.m. EST (1829 UTC) from pad 40 at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station.
